cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on image classification using a neural network architecture and training method. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training method and the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of biologically inspired visual processing filters, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of a linear classifier-stage output units, which could suggest it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of least squares regression to train the classifier output weights, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
